CONTEXT KleeneCycles IN ENGLISH

PURPOSE CONTEXT KleeneCycles MARKDOWN
{+ Cyclic graphs are where naive closure algorithms fail to terminate and
   where the transitive reduction collapses. Population: a 2-cycle {a,b},
   a 3-cycle {c,d,e}, a self-loop f, and a tail g entering the 2-cycle.

   Expected semantics:
   * r+ is the full relation on each strongly connected component, plus the
     reachability of the tail: 16 pairs, pinned exactly below.
   * r% is EMPTY: every edge on (or into) a cycle has a longer alternative
     path, so `r - (r;r+)` drops all of them. This pins the documented scope
     of r% (meaningful for acyclic relations only).
   * r* = I \/ r+ still holds, cycles or not.
+}

RELATION r[Node*Node]
POPULATION r CONTAINS
  [ ("a","b"), ("b","a")
  , ("c","d"), ("d","e"), ("e","c")
  , ("f","f")
  , ("g","a") ]

RELATION expectedPlus[Node*Node]
MEANING "Full closure: SCC {a,b} squared, SCC {c,d,e} squared, (f,f), and g's reach."
POPULATION expectedPlus CONTAINS
  [ ("a","a"), ("a","b"), ("b","a"), ("b","b")
  , ("c","c"), ("c","d"), ("c","e")
  , ("d","c"), ("d","d"), ("d","e")
  , ("e","c"), ("e","d"), ("e","e")
  , ("f","f")
  , ("g","a"), ("g","b") ]

RELATION expectedLoops[Node*Node]
MEANING "Exactly the atoms on a cycle appear on the diagonal of r+; g does not."
POPULATION expectedLoops CONTAINS
  [ ("a","a"), ("b","b"), ("c","c"), ("d","d"), ("e","e"), ("f","f") ]

RULE plusExact  : r+ = expectedPlus
RULE redEmpty   : r% |- -V[Node*Node]
RULE loopsExact : I[Node] /\ r+ = expectedLoops
RULE starLaw    : r* = I[Node] \/ r+
RULE plusUnfold : r+ = r \/ r;r+

INTERFACE Cycles : "_SESSION"[SESSION] ; V[SESSION*Node]
   CRud BOX<TABLE sortable>
   [ "node"  : I[Node]  cRud
   , "rStar" : r*       cRud
   , "rPlus" : r+       cRud
   , "rRed"  : r%       cRud
   ]

ENDCONTEXT
